Lionel Messi scored his 300th and
301st career goals for Barcelona as the Spanish soccer leader
rallied in the second half to beat Granada 2-1.  Odion Ighalo gave Granada the lead in the 26th minute and
Messi pulled Barcelona even early in the second half. Messi then
scored with a free kick in the 72nd minute, giving him 37 league
goals, and 48 in total, for the season.  The victory extends Bareclonaâ€™s lead La Liga to 15 points
over Atletico Madrid and 19 over Real Madrid. Atletico Madrid
plays Real Valladolid and Real Madrid hosts Rayo Vallecano
